Hey everyone! 👋 Here is a quick guide on how to set up and configure the ESP32 Smart Irrigation System before uploading it to your board.
First off, you need to configure your network credentials and security access keys. 
Just open the code and replace the placeholder text with your own local Wi-Fi network name and password in the Wi-Fi configuration section,
making sure your SSID and network password are correctly entered between the quotes.
Right below that, you will find the security section where you need to change the default access keys.
Make sure to update both user and admin passwords with your own secret strings to properly secure the web server interface and protect the admin panel from 
unauthorized access.
Once your credentials are set, you'll need to make sure you have the right libraries installed in your Arduino IDE.
The code relies on standard libraries:
EEPROM
WiFi
WebServer
 Wire
but you will also need to install the RTClib by Adafruit via the Library Manager to get the DS3231 real-time clock working properly.
That's pretty much it! Once everything is configured and uploaded, 
you'll have a fully working automated dual-pump irrigation system featuring an RTC clock,
a clean mobile-friendly web dashboard with dark mode support, and an admin panel to track your device status and recent connection logs.
Enjoy!
